{"lemma":"بِرِّ","slug":"بِرِّ","root":"ب.ر.ر","root_slug":"ب-ر-ر","root_link":"/words/roots/ب-ر-ر","pos":"N","pos_camel":"noun","paradigm":[],"frequency_in_corpus":0,"cross_references":{"qac":{"found":true,"lemma_key":"بِرّ","root":"برر","pos":"N","occurrence_count":8},"wiktextract":{"found":true,"entry_count":6,"pos_tags":["adj","noun","verb"],"has_etymology":true,"sense_count":18},"lanes":{"found":true,"entry_ids":["n2137","n2143","n2144","n2145"],"search_url":"https://lanelexicon.com/?s=%D8%A8%D9%90%D8%B1%D9%90%D9%91"}},"translations":null,"definition":{"source":"wiktextract","senses":[{"pos":"noun","gloss":"land, dry land (as opposed to sea)"},{"pos":"noun","gloss":"outside, field"},{"pos":"verb","gloss":"to be righteous, to be pious, to be godly, to be reverent, to be religious","tags":["intransitive"]},{"pos":"verb","gloss":"to be righteous, to be pious, to be godly, to be reverent, to be religious; to straighten up, to reform","tags":["intransitive"]},{"pos":"verb","gloss":"to be kind or generous to","tags":["intransitive"]},{"pos":"verb","gloss":"to respect or to be respectful [with بِ (bi) ‘to elders, one's parents or grandparents, old kinsmen, a deity, and so on’], to honor, to revere; to obey","tags":["intransitive","transitive"],"examples":[{"text":"بَرَّ الصَّبِيُّ وَالِدَيْهِ وَرَبَّهُ","english":"The boy obeyed his parents and his Lord."}]},{"pos":"verb","gloss":"to deem (an act) true, sincere, or pious; to accept or bless (a religious ritual)","tags":["transitive"],"examples":[{"text":"بَرَّ اللهُ حَجَّهُ وَصَلَاتَهُ","english":"Allah accepted his pilgrimage and his prayer."}]},{"pos":"verb","gloss":"to deem (an act) true, sincere, or pious; to accept or bless (a religious ritual); to be true, sincere, or pious","tags":["intransitive","transitive"],"examples":[{"text":"بَرَّ حَجُّهُ وَصَلَاتُهُ","english":"His pilgrimage and prayer were pious."}]},{"pos":"noun","gloss":"verbal noun of بَرَّ (barra) (form I)","tags":["form-of","noun-from-verb"]},{"pos":"noun","gloss":"faith, godliness, piety"},{"pos":"noun","gloss":"respectfulness"},{"pos":"noun","gloss":"kindness"},{"pos":"adj","gloss":"pious","examples":[{"text":"إِنَّ الْأَبْرَارَ لَفِي نَعِيمٍ / وَإِنَّ الْفُجَّارَ لَفِي جَحِيمٍ","english":"Indeed the pious will be in bliss, and lo, the wicked will be in the fire of hell."}]},{"pos":"adj","gloss":"pious; reverent, religious"},{"pos":"adj","gloss":"kind, benevolent"},{"pos":"adj","gloss":"respectful"},{"pos":"adj","gloss":"true, sincere"},{"pos":"noun","gloss":"wheat","tags":["Yemen","collective"],"examples":[{"text":"فخرجت إلى الساحل أربد بكلة وهذا أول الهند ومنتهى مسير المراكب لا يتهيّأ لها أن يتجاوزها وألا غرقت قال فلما وصلت إلى كلة رأيته وهي عظيمة عالية السور كثيرة البساتين غزيرة الماء ووجدت بها معدن الرصاص القلعي لا يكون إلا في قلعتها في سائر الدنيا، وفي هذه القلعة تضرب السيوف القلعية، وهي الهندية العتيقة … وأهل هذه القلعة يمتنعون على ملكها إذا أرادوا يطيعونه إن أحبوا ورسمهم رسم الصين في ترك الذبائح وليس في جميع الدنيا معدن الرصاص القلعي إلا في هذه القلعة وبينهما وبين الصين ثلثمائة فرسخ وحولها مدن ورساتيق وقرى ولهم أحكام وحبوس وخبايات وأكلهم البر والتمور وبقولهم كلها تباع وزنا وأرغفة خبزهم تباع عددا ولا حمامات لهم بل عندهم عين جارية يغتسلون فيها ودرهمهم يزن ثلثي درهم ويعرف بالفهري ولهم فلوس يتعاملون بها ويلبسون كأهل الصين الإفرند الصيني المثمن وملكها دون ملك الصين ويخطب لملك الصين وقبلته إليه وبيت عبادته له.","english":"And I went off to the dusty shore of Kala, which is the first and ultimate end of India for vessels, as nobody even dares to imagine to pass by it since he would drown. When I arrived at Kala, I conned it and it is large and has high walls, many gardens and plenty of water, and I found mines of tin not found in the rest of the world but in Qalʕa, and in this Qalʕa one forges the Qalʕaite swords, the excellent Indian ones, and the populace of this Qalʕa withstands its king when it wants and abides by him when it lists, and their tradition is like the tradition of China, refraining from slaughtering beasts, and there aren’t in all the world tin mines but in this Qalʕa, and between them two and China are three-hundred parasang, and there are towns, rural districts and villages, and they have jurisdiction, jails, and corbans, and their food is wheat and dates and all their vegetables they buy by scales, and their bread is bread-rolls they buy by count. They have no baths but a running spring in which they wash, and their dirham weighs as a third-dirham and is known as Fahrī, and they have fulūs with which they commerce, and they dress like the people of China in dear Chinese silks, and their king is subordinate to the King of China, reports to the King of China, his praying direction is to him, his place of sacrifice is towards him."},{"text":"فاتفق أن أمية بن أبي الصلت مر على بني عبد المدان، فرأى طعامهم لباب البر والشهد.","english":"There has been agreement that Umayya ibn Abī s-Salt passed by the Banū ʕabd al-Madān and he saw that they ate pulp of wheat and honey."}]}]},"etymology":{"source":"wiktextract","text":"From the root ب ر ر (b r r). Inherited from Proto-Semitic *barr-.\n\nProbably one of the words Yemenite expatriates picked up in the Byzantine Empire, from Ancient Greek πυρός (purós), similar to فِرْسِك (firsik, “peach”), if it is correct that one has to posit for Proto-Indo-European *péh₂wr̥ a meaning “spelt”. Another word for spelt or dinkel wheat is borrowed from Ancient Greek: خَنْدَرُوس (ḵandarūs).\nThe similar Hebrew בָּר (bār, “grain, corn”) may be instead from the same derivation as the etymon of بَزْر (bazr, “seed”). The similarity to Proto-Slavic *bъrъ (“foxtail millet”) is also likely a coincidence."},"ipa":null,"lanes_definition":{"source":"lanes","entries":[{"entry_id":"n2137","headword_ar":"بَرَّ","root":"br","body":[{"kind":"text","text":", [first pers."},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"barirotu","text_ar":"بَرِرْتُ"},{"kind":"text","text":",] aor."},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"yabar~u","text_ar":"يَبَرُّ"},{"kind":"text","text":", (T, M, Msb,) inf. n."},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"bir~N","text_ar":"بِرٌّ"},{"kind":"text","text":", (M, Msb, K,)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"He was pious"},{"kind":"text","text":"["},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"towards his father"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"parents,"},{"kind":"text","text":"and (tropical:)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"towards God;"},{"kind":"text","text":"(see the explanations of the verb as used transitively;) and"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"was kind,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"good and affectionate and gentle in behaviour, towards his kindred;"},{"kind":"text","text":"and"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"kind,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"good, in his dealings with strangers"},{"kind":"text","text":"]: (Msb:)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"he was good, just, righteous, virtuous,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"honest:"},{"kind":"text","text":"(T, Msb:) [or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"he was amply, largely,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"extensively, good"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"beneficent:"},{"kind":"text","text":"] and"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"he was true,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"veracious."},{"kind":"text","text":"(M, Msb, K.) [Authorities differ as to the primary signification of this verb, and as to the subordinate meanings: see"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"bir~N","text_ar":"بِرٌّ"},{"kind":"text","text":"below.] You say also,"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"bar~a fiY qawolihi","text_ar":"بَرَّ فِى قَوْلِهِ"},{"kind":"text","text":", (Msb, TA,) and"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"fiY yamiynihi","text_ar":"فِى يَمِينِهِ"},{"kind":"text","text":", (S, M, Mgh, Msb, K,) first pers."},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"barirotu","text_ar":"بَرِرْتُ"},{"kind":"text","text":"(T, A, Mgh, K) and"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"bararotu","text_ar":"بَرَرْتُ"},{"kind":"text","text":", (K,) aor."},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"yabar~u","text_ar":"يَبَرُّ"},{"kind":"text","text":"(M, Msb) and"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"yabir~N","text_ar":"يَبِرٌّ"},{"kind":"text","text":", (M,) inf. n."},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"bir~N","text_ar":"بِرٌّ"},{"kind":"text","text":"(S, M, K) and"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"bar~N","text_ar":"بَرٌّ"},{"kind":"text","text":", (K,) or"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"buruwrN","text_ar":"بُرُورٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":", (Msb,)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"He was true,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"veracious,"},{"kind":"text","text":"(S, Mgh, Msb, K, TA,)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"in his saying,"},{"kind":"text","text":"(Msb, TA,) and"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"in his oath."},{"kind":"text","text":"(S, Mgh, Msb, K.) ―         -b2-"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"bar~a Eamalahu","text_ar":"بَرَّ عَمَلَهُ"},{"kind":"text","text":", and"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"bur~a","text_ar":"بُرَّ"},{"kind":"text","text":", inf. n."},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"bir~N","text_ar":"بِرٌّ"},{"kind":"text","text":"and"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"buruwrN","text_ar":"بُرُورٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":"; and ↓"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"A^abar~a","text_ar":"اَبَرَّ","orth_type":"arrow"},{"kind":"text","text":"; ["},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"His deed,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"work, was,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"proved, good;"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"was well,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"sinlessly, performed;"},{"kind":"text","text":"] all signify the same. (M.) And"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"bur~a AlEamalu","text_ar":"بُرَّ العَمَلُ"},{"kind":"text","text":", i. e."},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"AlHaj~u","text_ar":"الحَجُّ"},{"kind":"text","text":", a form of benediction, said to a person come from pilgrimage,"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"May the deed,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"work,"},{"kind":"text","text":"i. e. the pilgrimage,"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"have been sinlessly performed."},{"kind":"text","text":"(TA.) And"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"bar~a Haj~uhu","text_ar":"بَرَّ حَجُّهُ"},{"kind":"text","text":", (T, S, A, Msb, K,) aor."},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"yabar~u","text_ar":"يَبَرُّ"},{"kind":"text","text":", (T,) inf. n."},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"bir~N","text_ar":"بِرٌّ"},{"kind":"text","text":"(S, Msb,) or"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"buruwrN","text_ar":"بُرُورٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":"; (T;) and"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"bur~a Haj~uhu","text_ar":"بُرَّ حَجُّهُ"},{"kind":"text","text":", (Fr, T, S, M, K,) aor."},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"yubar~u","text_ar":"يُبَرُّ"},{"kind":"text","text":", inf. n."},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"bir~N","text_ar":"بِرٌّ"},{"kind":"text","text":"; (T;)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"His pilgrimage was sinlessly performed:"},{"kind":"text","text":"(Sh, T:) or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"was characterized by the giving of food, and by sweetness of speech;"},{"kind":"text","text":"as explained by Mohammad himself:"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"was accepted: was rewarded."},{"kind":"text","text":"(TA.) ―         -b3-"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"bar~a","text_ar":"بَرَّ"},{"kind":"text","text":", (A, Msb, K,) aor."},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"yabar~u","text_ar":"يَبَرُّ"},{"kind":"text","text":"(T, M, K) and"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"yabir~u","text_ar":"يَبِرُّ"},{"kind":"text","text":", (M, K,) inf. n."},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"bir~N","text_ar":"بِرٌّ"},{"kind":"text","text":"(M, Msb, K) and"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"bar~N","text_ar":"بَرٌّ"},{"kind":"text","text":"and"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"buruwrN","text_ar":"بُرُورٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":", (M, K,)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"It"},{"kind":"text","text":"(a saying, Msb, and an oath, T, A, M, Msb, K)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"was,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"proved, true."},{"kind":"text","text":"(M, A, * Msb, * K, * TA.) [See an ex. voce"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"A^aliy~apN","text_ar":"اَلِيَّةٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":", in art."},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"Alw","text_ar":"الو"},{"kind":"text","text":".] ―         -b4-"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"bar~ato","text_ar":"بَرَّتْ"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"biY siloEatuhu","text_ar":"بِى سِلْعَتُهُ"},{"kind":"text","text":", inf. n."},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"bir~N","text_ar":"بِرٌّ"},{"kind":"text","text":", (tropical:)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"His commodity,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"article of merchandise, was easy of sale to me,"},{"kind":"text","text":"(Aboo-Sa'eed, T, A, *)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"and procured me gain:"},{"kind":"text","text":"(A:) originally meaning"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"it recompensed me,"},{"kind":"text","text":"by its high price, for my care of it. (T.) [See also"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"bar~ahu","text_ar":"بَرَّهُ"},{"kind":"text","text":", below.]       -A2-"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"bar~a waAlidahu","text_ar":"بَرَّ وَالِدَهُ"},{"kind":"text","text":", (M,) [and app."},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"biwaAlidihi","text_ar":"بِوَالِدِهِ"},{"kind":"text","text":", (see"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"bar~N","text_ar":"بَرٌّ"},{"kind":"text","text":",)] first pers."},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"barirotu","text_ar":"بَرِرْتُ"},{"kind":"text","text":"(S, M, Msb, K) and"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"bararotu","text_ar":"بَرَرْتُ"},{"kind":"text","text":", (M, K,) aor."},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"yabar~u","text_ar":"يَبَرُّ"},{"kind":"text","text":"(S, M, Msb, K) and"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"yabir~u","text_ar":"يَبِرُّ"},{"kind":"text","text":", (M, K,) inf. n."},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"bir~N","text_ar":"بِرٌّ"},{"kind":"text","text":"(S, M, Msb, K) and"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"mabar~apN","text_ar":"مَبَرَّةٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":"(S, K, Msb *) and"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"buruwrN","text_ar":"بُرُورٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":", (Msb,)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"He treated,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"behaved towards, his father with filial piety, duty,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"obedience;"},{"kind":"text","text":"(TA;) or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"with ample obedience;"},{"kind":"text","text":"(B;) the inf. ns. signifying the"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"contr. of"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"EuquwqN","text_ar":"عُقُوقٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":": (S, M, A, K:)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"he treated,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"behaved towards, his father with good obedience, and with gentleness,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"courtesy, striving to do the things that were pleasing to him, and to avoid what were displeasing to him."},{"kind":"text","text":"(Msb.) And [hence, app., for accord. to the A it is tropical.]"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"bar~a xaAliqahu","text_ar":"بَرَّ خَالِقَهُ"},{"kind":"text","text":", (S,) or"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"rab~ahu","text_ar":"رَبَّهُ"},{"kind":"text","text":", (A,) aor."},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"yabar~u","text_ar":"يَبَرُّ"},{"kind":"text","text":", (S, A,) inf. n."},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"bir~N","text_ar":"بِرٌّ"},{"kind":"text","text":"; (T, S, M, K;) and ↓"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"tbr~rhu","text_ar":"تبرّرهُ","orth_type":"arrow"},{"kind":"text","text":"; (S, K; *) (tropical:)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"He obeyed his Creator,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"his Lord;"},{"kind":"text","text":"(S, M, * A, K; *) ["},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"was pious towards Him;"},{"kind":"text","text":"]"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"served Him; rendered religious service to Him:"},{"kind":"text","text":"(TA:) or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"rendered Him ample obedience:"},{"kind":"text","text":"the obedience here meant is of two kinds; namely, that of belief and that of works; and both these kinds are meant by"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"Albir~","text_ar":"البِرّ"},{"kind":"text","text":"in the Kur ii. 172. (B.) [And app."},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"bar~ato","text_ar":"بَرَّتْ"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"waladahaA","text_ar":"وَلَدَهَا"},{"kind":"text","text":", or"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"biwaladihaA","text_ar":"بِوَلَدِهَا"},{"kind":"text","text":","},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"She behaved with maternal affection towards her child,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"offspring."},{"kind":"text","text":"(See"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"bar~N","text_ar":"بَرٌّ"},{"kind":"text","text":".)] And"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"bar~ahu","text_ar":"بَرَّهُ"},{"kind":"text","text":", (M,) and"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"bar~a raHimahu","text_ar":"بَرَّ رَحِمَهُ"},{"kind":"text","text":", (T,) first pers."},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"barirotu","text_ar":"بَرِرْتُ"},{"kind":"text","text":", (T, M,) inf. n."},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"bir~N","text_ar":"بِرٌّ"},{"kind":"text","text":", (T, M, K,)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"He behaved towards him,"},{"kind":"text","text":"and"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"towards his kindred,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"relations, with kindness,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"goodness and affection and gentleness, and regard for his,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"their, circumstances;"},{"kind":"text","text":"syn."},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"waSalahu","text_ar":"وَصَلَهُ"},{"kind":"text","text":"[and"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"waSalahumo","text_ar":"وَصَلَهُمْ"},{"kind":"text","text":"]: (T, M, K:) such is said to be the signification of the verb as use in the Kur lx. 8. (M, B, TA. [See also 3.]) And"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"Aall~`hu yabar~u EibaAdahu","text_ar":"اَللّٰهُ يَبَرُّ عِبَادَهُ"},{"kind":"text","text":"(assumed tropical:)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"God is merciful to his servants:"},{"kind":"text","text":"(M, TA:) or"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"bar~ahu","text_ar":"بَرَّهُ"},{"kind":"text","text":", inf. n."},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"bir~N","text_ar":"بِرٌّ"},{"kind":"text","text":", said of God, means"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"He recompensed him,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"rewarded him, for his obedience."},{"kind":"text","text":"(B, TA.) ["},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"bar~ahu bika*aA","text_ar":"بَرَّهُ بِكَذَا"},{"kind":"text","text":"(occurring in the S and K in explanation of"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"A^aloTafahu bika*aA","text_ar":"اَلْطَفَهُ بِكَذَا"},{"kind":"text","text":") may be rendered"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"He showed kindness,"},{"kind":"text","text":"&c.,"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"to him by such a thing,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"such an action,"},{"kind":"text","text":"&c.: and also"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"he presented him with such a thing;"},{"kind":"text","text":"like"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"waSalahu","text_ar":"وَصَلَهُ"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"bika*aA","text_ar":"بِكَذَا"},{"kind":"text","text":".] ―         -b2-"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"bar~a A@ll~`hu Haj~ahu","text_ar":"بَرَّ ا@للّٰهُ حَجَّهُ"},{"kind":"text","text":", (T, S, Msb,) aor."},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"yabar~u","text_ar":"يَبَرُّ"},{"kind":"text","text":", (Msb,) inf. n."},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"bir~N","text_ar":"بِرٌّ"},{"kind":"text","text":", (S,) or"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"buruwrN","text_ar":"بُرُورٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":", (Msb,)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"God accepted his pilgrimage;"},{"kind":"text","text":"(S, Msb;) as also ↓"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"Abr~hu","text_ar":"ابرّهُ","orth_type":"arrow"},{"kind":"text","text":": (T, S, M, Msb:) the latter alone is allowed by Fr: (M, TA:) [though"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"bur~a Haj~uhu","text_ar":"بُرَّ حَجُّهُ"},{"kind":"text","text":"and"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"Eamaluhu","text_ar":"عَمَلُهُ"},{"kind":"text","text":", mentioned above, are well known; as is the pass. part. n."},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"maboruwrN","text_ar":"مَبْرُورٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":", which see below:] and one says, [in like manner,]"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"A@ll~`hu Eamaluhu","text_ar":"ا@للّٰهُ عَمَلُهُ"},{"kind":"text","text":"↓"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"Abr~","text_ar":"ابرّ","orth_type":"arrow"},{"kind":"text","text":"["},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"God accepted his deed,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"work, as good; approved it"},{"kind":"text","text":"]. (M.) ―         -b3-  See also 4, in three places.       -A3-"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"bar~a","text_ar":"بَرَّ"},{"kind":"text","text":", (TK,) inf. n."},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"bir~N","text_ar":"بِرٌّ"},{"kind":"text","text":", (S, K,)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"He drove"},{"kind":"text","text":"sheep or goats: (IAar, S, K:) or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"he called"},{"kind":"text","text":"them. (Yoo.) [See also"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"bir~N","text_ar":"بِرٌّ"},{"kind":"text","text":"below.]"}],"source_refs":["T","M","Msb","K","TA","S","Mgh","A","Fr","Sh","TK","IAar"]},{"entry_id":"n2143","headword_ar":"بَرٌّ","root":"br","body":[{"kind":"text","text":"[originally"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"barirN","text_ar":"بَرِرٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":"] (M, Msb, K) and ↓"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"baAr~N","text_ar":"بَارٌّ","orth_type":"arrow"},{"kind":"text","text":"(Msb)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"Pious"},{"kind":"text","text":"["},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"towards his father"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"parents,"},{"kind":"text","text":"and (tropical:)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"towards God;"},{"kind":"text","text":"(tropical:)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"obedient to God, serving God,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"rendering religious service to God;"},{"kind":"text","text":"(see 1;) and"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"kind,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"good and affectionate and gentle in behaviour, towards his kindred;"},{"kind":"text","text":"and"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"good in his dealings with strangers"},{"kind":"text","text":"];"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"good, just, righteous, virtuous,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"honest:"},{"kind":"text","text":"(Msb:)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"true,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"veracious:"},{"kind":"text","text":"(M, Msb, K:) and both signify also"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"abounding in"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"bir~","text_ar":"بِرّ"},{"kind":"text","text":"[or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"filial piety,"},{"kind":"text","text":"&c.]: (K:) the former is [said to be] a stronger epithet than the latter, like as"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"EadolN","text_ar":"عَدْلٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":"is stronger than"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"EaAdilN","text_ar":"عَادِلٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":": (B:) [but its pl. shows that it is not, like"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"EadolN","text_ar":"عَدْلٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":", originally an inf. n.: it is a regular contraction of"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"barirN","text_ar":"بَرِرٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":", like as"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"baAr~N","text_ar":"بَارٌّ"},{"kind":"text","text":"is of"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"baArirN","text_ar":"بَارِرٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":":] the fem. of each is with"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"p","text_ar":"ة"},{"kind":"text","text":": (Lh, M:) the pl. (of the former, S, M, Msb, or of the latter, B) is"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"A^aboraAN","text_ar":"اَبْرَاٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":"; and (of the latter, S, M, Msb, or of the former, B)"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"bararapN","text_ar":"بَرَرَةٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":": (S, M, Msb, K:) the former pl. is often specially applied to saints, those who abstain from worldly pleasures, and devotees; and the latter, to the recording angels. (B.) You say,"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"A^anaA bar~N biwaAlidiY","text_ar":"اَنَا بَرٌّ بِوَالِدِى"},{"kind":"text","text":", and ↓"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"baAr~N","text_ar":"بَارٌّ","orth_type":"arrow"},{"kind":"text","text":","},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"I am characterized by filial piety, dutifulness,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"obedience, to my father:"},{"kind":"text","text":"(S, M, A: *) the latter is mentioned on the authority of Kr; but some disallow it. (M, TA.) And"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"AlA^um~u bar~apN biwaladihaA","text_ar":"الاُمُّ بَرَّةٌ بِوَلَدِهَا"},{"kind":"text","text":"["},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"The mother is maternally affectionate to her child,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"offspring"},{"kind":"text","text":"]. (S.) And"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"rajulN bar~N bi*iY qaraAbatihi","text_ar":"رَجُلٌ بَرٌّ بِذِى قَرَابَتِهِ"},{"kind":"text","text":", and ↓"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"baAr~N","text_ar":"بَارٌّ","orth_type":"arrow"},{"kind":"text","text":","},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"A man who behaves towards his kindred with kindness,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"goodness and affection and gentleness, and regard for their circumstances."},{"kind":"text","text":"(T.) And"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"rajulN bar~N sar~N","text_ar":"رَجُلٌ بَرٌّ سَرٌّ"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"A man who treats with goodness and affection and gentleness, and rejoices,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"gladdens, his brethren:"},{"kind":"text","text":"pl."},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"bar~uwna sar~uwna","text_ar":"بَرُّونَ سَرُّونَ"},{"kind":"text","text":". (S, * K, * TA, in art."},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"sr","text_ar":"سر"},{"kind":"text","text":".) And"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"bar~N fiY qawolK","text_ar":"بَرٌّ فِى قَوْلٍ"},{"kind":"text","text":", and"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"fiY yamiynK","text_ar":"فِى يَمِينٍ"},{"kind":"text","text":", and ↓"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"baAr~N","text_ar":"بَارٌّ","orth_type":"arrow"},{"kind":"text","text":","},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"True,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"veracious, in a saying,"},{"kind":"text","text":"and"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"in an oath."},{"kind":"text","text":"(Msb.) And"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"yamiynN bar~apN","text_ar":"يَمِينٌ بَرَّةٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":"and ↓"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"baAr~apN","text_ar":"بَارَّةٌ","orth_type":"arrow"},{"kind":"text","text":"["},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"A true oath;"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"an oath that proves true"},{"kind":"text","text":"]. (Ham p. 811.)"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"Albar~u","text_ar":"البَرُّ"},{"kind":"text","text":"is also a name of God; (M, K;) meaning (assumed tropical:)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"The Merciful,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"Compassionate:"},{"kind":"text","text":"(M:) or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"the Very Benign to his servants;"},{"kind":"text","text":"(IAth;)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"the Ample in goodness"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"beneficence:"},{"kind":"text","text":"(B:)"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"AlbaAr~u","text_ar":"البَارُّ"},{"kind":"text","text":"is not so used. (IAth.) It is said in a trad.,"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"tamas~aHuwA biAlA^aroDi faA_in~ahaA bar~apN bikumo","text_ar":"تَمَسَّحُوا بِالاَرْضِ فَاـِنَّهَا بَرَّةٌ بِكُمْ"},{"kind":"text","text":"(assumed tropical:)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"Wipe yourselves with the dust,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"earth,"},{"kind":"text","text":"[in performing the ceremony termed"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"Alt~ayam~umu","text_ar":"التَّيَمُّمُ"},{"kind":"text","text":",]"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"for it is benignant towards you,"},{"kind":"text","text":"like as the mother is to her children; meaning, ye are created from it, and in it are your means of subsistence, and to it ye return after death: (IAth:) or the meaning is, that your tents, or houses, are upon it, and ye are buried in it. (M.)       -A2-"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"bar~N","text_ar":"بَرٌّ"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"Land;"},{"kind":"text","text":"opposed to"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"baHorN","text_ar":"بَحْرٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":"[as meaning “ sea ” and the like]: (S, Msb, K:) from"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"bir~N","text_ar":"بِرٌّ"},{"kind":"text","text":"signifying “ ampleness, ” “ largeness, ” or “ extensiveness; ” (Esh-Shiháb [El-Khafájee], MF;) or the former word is the original of the latter. (B, TA. [See the latter word.]) [Hence,"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"bar~FA wa baHorFA","text_ar":"بَرًّا وَ بَحْرًا"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"By land and by sea."},{"kind":"text","text":"] ―         -b2-"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"A desert,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"deserts; a waste,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"wastes."},{"kind":"text","text":"(T, TA. [See also"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"bar~iy~apN","text_ar":"بَرِّيَّةٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":", voce"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"bar~iy~N","text_ar":"بَرِّيٌّ"},{"kind":"text","text":".]) So, accord. to Mujáhid [and the Jel] in words of the Kur [vi. 59],"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"wa yaEolamu maA fiY Albar~i wa AlbaHori","text_ar":"وَ يَعْلَمُ مَا فِى البَرِّ وَ البَحْرِ"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"And He knoweth what is in the desert,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"deserts, and the towns,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"villages, in which is water,"},{"kind":"text","text":"(T, TA,) or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"which are upon the rivers."},{"kind":"text","text":"(Jel.) [So too in the phrase"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"nabaAtu Albar~i","text_ar":"نَبَاتُ البَرِّ"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"The plants,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"herbage, of the desert"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"waste; the wild plants"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"herbage."},{"kind":"text","text":"And"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"Easalu Albar~i","text_ar":"عَسَلُ البَرِّ"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"Honey of the desert; wild honey."},{"kind":"text","text":"And"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"HayawaAnu Albar~i","text_ar":"حَيَوَانُ البَرِّ"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"The animal,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"animals, of the desert; the wild animal"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"animals."},{"kind":"text","text":"] ―         -b3-"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"A wide tract of land."},{"kind":"text","text":"(Bd in ii. 41.) ―         -b4-  [The"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"open country;"},{"kind":"text","text":"opposed to"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"baHorN","text_ar":"بَحْرٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":"as meaning the “ cities, ” or “ towns, ” “ upon the rivers: ” see the latter word.] ―         -b5-"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"Elevated ground, open to view."},{"kind":"text","text":"(T.) ―         -b6-  The"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"tract, or part, out of doors,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"where one is exposed to view; contr. of"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"kin~N","text_ar":"كِنٌّ"},{"kind":"text","text":": used by the Arabs indeterminately; [without the article"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"Al","text_ar":"ال"},{"kind":"text","text":";] as in the phrase,"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"jalasotu bar~FA","text_ar":"جَلَسْتُ بَرًّا"},{"kind":"text","text":"(Lth, T) meaning"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"I sat outside the house;"},{"kind":"text","text":"(A;) and"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"xarajotu bar~FA","text_ar":"خَرَجْتُ بَرًّا"},{"kind":"text","text":"(Lth, T) meaning"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"I went forth outside the"},{"kind":"text","text":"["},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"house"},{"kind":"text","text":"or]"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"town,"},{"kind":"text","text":"(A,) or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"into the desert:"},{"kind":"text","text":"(TA:) but [Az says,] these are post-classical phrases, which I have not heard from the chaste-speaking Arabs of the desert. (T.) ―         -b7-  You say also,"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"A^ariydu jaw~FA wa yuriydu bar~FA","text_ar":"اَرِيدُ جَوًّا وَ يُرِيدُ بَرًّا"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"I desire concealment,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"secrecy, and he desires publicity."},{"kind":"text","text":"(A.)"}],"source_refs":["M","Msb","K","B","Lh","S","IAth","T","TA","Lth","A"]},{"entry_id":"n2144","headword_ar":"بُرٌّ","root":"br","body":[{"kind":"italic_en","text":"Wheat;"},{"kind":"text","text":"and the"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"grain of wheat;"},{"kind":"text","text":"syn."},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"qamoHN","text_ar":"قَمْحٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":", (S, * Msb,) or"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"HinoTapN","text_ar":"حِنْطَةٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":"; (M, K;) but it is a more chaste word than"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"qamoHN","text_ar":"قَمْحٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":"and"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"HinoTapN","text_ar":"حِنْطَةٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":": (M:) pl. of"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"bur~apN","text_ar":"بُرَّةٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":"; (S, M;) or [rather]"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"bur~apN","text_ar":"بُرَّةٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":"is the n. un. [signifying"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"a grain of wheat,"},{"kind":"text","text":"like"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"qamoHapN","text_ar":"قَمْحَةٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":"]: (IDrd, Msb:) the pl. of"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"bur~N","text_ar":"بُرٌّ"},{"kind":"text","text":"is"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"A^aboraArN","text_ar":"اَبْرَارٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":"; (K;) or this pl. is allowable on the ground of analogy, accord. to Mbr, but is disallowed by Sb. (S.) It is said in a prov., (TA,)"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"huwa A^aqoSaru mino br~apK","text_ar":"هُوَ اَقْصَرُ مِنْ برَّةٍ"},{"kind":"text","text":"["},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"He,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"it, is shorter than a grain of wheat"},{"kind":"text","text":"]. (A, TA.) And you say,"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"A^aToEmanaA A@bona bur~apK","text_ar":"اَطْعمَنَا ا@بْنَ بُرَّةٍ"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"He fed us with bread."},{"kind":"text","text":"(A.)"}],"source_refs":["M","IDrd","Msb","TA"]},{"entry_id":"n2145","headword_ar":"بِرٌّ","root":"br","body":[{"kind":"text","text":"inf. n. of 1: (T, S, M, &c.:) it is said by some to signify primarily"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"Ampleness, largeness,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"extensiveness;"},{"kind":"text","text":"whence"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"bar~N","text_ar":"بَرٌّ"},{"kind":"text","text":"as opposed to"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"baHorN","text_ar":"بَحْرٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":": then, ―         -b2-"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"Benevolent and solicitous regard"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"treatment"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"conduct"},{"kind":"text","text":"["},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"to parents and others;"},{"kind":"text","text":"i. e."},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"piety to parents;"},{"kind":"text","text":"and (tropical:)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"towards God"},{"kind":"text","text":"]: and"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"goodness,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"beneficence:"},{"kind":"text","text":"and"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"kindness,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"good and affectionate and gentle behaviour, and regard for the circumstances of another:"},{"kind":"text","text":"(Esh-Shiháb [El-Khafájee], MF:) or"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"bar~N","text_ar":"بَرٌّ"},{"kind":"text","text":", as opposed to"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"baHorN","text_ar":"بَحْرٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":", [or as signifying “ a wide tract of land, ” (Bd in ii. 41,)] is the original of"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"bir~N","text_ar":"بِرٌّ"},{"kind":"text","text":", (Bd in ii. 41, B, TA,) which signifies"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"ample, large,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"extensive, goodness"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"beneficence,"},{"kind":"text","text":"(Z, in the Ksh, ii. 41, [but he regards it as the original of"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"bar~N","text_ar":"بَرٌّ"},{"kind":"text","text":",] and Bd on the same passage, and B, K, TA,)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"to men;"},{"kind":"text","text":"(TA;) or comprehending"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"every kind of goodness:"},{"kind":"text","text":"(Ksh and Bd ubi suprà:) and hence it is said to be in three things:"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"in the service of God: in paying regard to relations; acting well to them:"},{"kind":"text","text":"and"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"in dealing with strangers:"},{"kind":"text","text":"(Bd ubi suprà:) or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"every deed that is approved:"},{"kind":"text","text":"(Ksh and Bd in ii. 172:) and [particularly]"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"obedience to God:"},{"kind":"text","text":"(T, S, M, &c.: [see also"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"bar~apu","text_ar":"بَرَّةُ"},{"kind":"text","text":":]) [and"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"every incumbent duty:"},{"kind":"text","text":"and hence,] the"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"pilgrimage to Mekkeh:"},{"kind":"text","text":"(K:) and"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"fidelity to an engagement:"},{"kind":"text","text":"(TA:) also"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"a gratuitous gift,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"favour;"},{"kind":"text","text":"and"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"a bounty,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"benefit;"},{"kind":"text","text":"syn."},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"faDolN","text_ar":"فَضْلٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":"; (Msb;) and"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"A_iHosaAnN","text_ar":"اـِحْسَانٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":"; as also ↓"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"mabar~apN","text_ar":"مَبَرَّةٌ","orth_type":"arrow"},{"kind":"text","text":"[an inf. n., but when used as a simple subst. its pl. is"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"mabaArN","text_ar":"مَبَارٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":"and"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"mabar~aAtN","text_ar":"مَبَرَّاتٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":"]. (Har p. 94.) In the Kur [ii. 172], where it is said,"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"lukin~a Albir~a mano A=mana biAA@ll~`hi","text_ar":"لُكِنَّ البِرَّ مَنْ ا=مَنَ بِاا@للّٰهِ"},{"kind":"text","text":", by"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"Albr~","text_ar":"البرّ"},{"kind":"text","text":"is meant"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"*aA Albir~i","text_ar":"ذَا البِرِّ"},{"kind":"text","text":"[i. e."},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"But the pious,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"obedient"},{"kind":"text","text":"to God,"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"is he who believeth in God"},{"kind":"text","text":"]; (T, M, Ksh, Bd, Jel;) and some read"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"AlbaAr~a","text_ar":"البَارَّ"},{"kind":"text","text":": (Ksh, Bd, Jel:) or the meaning is,"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"lkn~ Albir~a bir~u mn A=mn","text_ar":"لكنّ البِرَّ بِرُّ من ا=من"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"bA ll~`h","text_ar":"با للّٰه"},{"kind":"text","text":"i. e."},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"but the obedience"},{"kind":"text","text":"of which it behooveth one to be mindful"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"is the obedience of him who believeth in God:"},{"kind":"text","text":"(Sb, T, IJ, M, Ksh, Bd:) and this explanation is preferable to the former. (Bd.) It is said in a prov., (T, S,)"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"laA yaEorifu hir~FA mino birK","text_ar":"لَا يَعْرِفُ هِرًّا مِنْ بِرٍ"},{"kind":"text","text":", (S, A, K, but in the T and M"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"maA","text_ar":"مَا"},{"kind":"text","text":"is put in the place of"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"lA","text_ar":"لا"},{"kind":"text","text":",) meaning"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"He knows not him who dislikes him,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"hates him, from him who behaves"},{"kind":"page_break","n":177},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"towards him with kindness,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"goodness and affection and gentleness, and regard for his circumstances:"},{"kind":"text","text":"(S, M, A, K, * TA:) or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"undutiful conduct to a parent from gentleness,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"courtesy:"},{"kind":"text","text":"(ElFezáree, T, K:) or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"altercation,"},{"kind":"text","text":"(T,) or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"dislike,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"hatred,"},{"kind":"text","text":"(K,)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"from honourable treatment:"},{"kind":"text","text":"(T, K:) or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"the calling of sheep,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"goats, from the driving of them:"},{"kind":"text","text":"(IAar, S, K:) or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"the driving of sheep,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"goats, from the calling of them:"},{"kind":"text","text":"(Yoo, T:) or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"the calling of them to water from the calling of them to fodder;"},{"kind":"text","text":"(K;) which last rendering is agreeable with an explanation of"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"bir~N","text_ar":"بِرٌّ"},{"kind":"text","text":"by IAar [mentioned in the T]; (TA;) and ↓"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"birobirN","text_ar":"بِرْبِرٌ","orth_type":"arrow"},{"kind":"text","text":", also, has the signification here assigned to"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"bir~N","text_ar":"بِرٌّ"},{"kind":"text","text":": (K, * TA:) or"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"Alharoharap","text_ar":"الهَرْهَرَة"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"from"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"Albarobarap","text_ar":"البَرْبَرَة"},{"kind":"text","text":"; (A'Obeyd, T, K;) i. e."},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"the crying of sheep from the crying of goats:"},{"kind":"text","text":"(A'Obeyd, T:) or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"the cat from the rat,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"mouse:"},{"kind":"text","text":"(IAar, T, M, K:) and"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"bir~N","text_ar":"بِرٌّ"},{"kind":"text","text":"also signifies the ["},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"species of rat called"},{"kind":"text","text":"]"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"jura*","text_ar":"جُرَذ"},{"kind":"text","text":": (Aboo-Tálib, T, K:) or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"a small animal resembling the rat"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"mouse:"},{"kind":"text","text":"(M:) and the"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"young of the fox."},{"kind":"text","text":"(K.) ―         -b3-  Also"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"Good,"},{"kind":"text","text":"as a subst., not an adj.; syn."},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"xayorN","text_ar":"خَيْرٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":"; (Sh, T, Mgh, Msb, K;) which comprises all that has been said in explanation of"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"bir~N","text_ar":"بِرٌّ"},{"kind":"text","text":"(Sh, T, Mgh) as used in the saying of Mohammad,"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"Ealyokumo biAlS~idoqi faA_in~ahu yahodiY","text_ar":"عَليْكُمْ بِالصِّدْقِ فَاـِنَّهُ يَهْدِى"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"A_ilaY Albir~i","text_ar":"اـِلَى البِرِّ"},{"kind":"text","text":"["},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"Keep ye to truth; for it guides to good,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"to a good,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"right, state"},{"kind":"text","text":"]: some render it in this instance by"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"Alxayor","text_ar":"الخَيْر"},{"kind":"text","text":"; and some, by"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"AlS~alaAH","text_ar":"الصَّلَاح"},{"kind":"text","text":". (Sh, T.) It signifies also The"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"good of the present life, consisting in spiritual and worldly blessings, and of that which is to come, consisting in everlasting enjoyment in Paradise:"},{"kind":"text","text":"so in the Kur iii. 86: (T:) or [simply]"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"Paradise."},{"kind":"text","text":"(K.) ―         -b4-  Also The"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"heart;"},{"kind":"text","text":"or the"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"mind."},{"kind":"text","text":"(K.) So in the saying,"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"huwa muTomay^in~u Albir~i","text_ar":"هُوَ مُطْمَيِنُّ البِرِّ"},{"kind":"text","text":"["},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"He is quiet,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"at rest, in heart,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"mind"},{"kind":"text","text":"]. (TA.)"}],"source_refs":["K","TA","Ksh","Bd","Jel","Sb","T","IJ","M","S","IAar","Yoo","Sh","Mgh"]}]},"classical_definitions":null}